  "response": "Yes, California has voted for Republican candidates in general elections. Historically, California has supported Republican presidential candidates at various times. For example, California voted for Ronald Reagan in both the 1980 and 1984 presidential elections, and for George H.W. Bush in the 1988 presidential election. However, in recent decades, California has leaned more towards Democratic candidates, consistently voting for them in presidential elections since 1992.",
